tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows evidence of renal impairment (elevated creatinine), mild hypoglycemia, and proteinuria with glucosuria and ketonuria, suggesting possible renal tubular dysfunction or diabetes with poor glycemic control, though HbA1c is unexpectedly low. Urine is abnormal in appearance and specific gravity is low, indicating possible impaired concentrating ability. No evidence of urinary infection. Further clinical correlation and nephrology evaluation are recommended.
